{"id":1323,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::fs\n```\n\n```rust\npub struct OpenOptions\n```\n\n---\n\nOptions and flags which can be used to configure how a file is opened.\n\nThis builder exposes the ability to configure how a [`File`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/fs/struct.File.html) is opened and\nwhat operations are permitted on the open file. The [`File::open`](`File::open`) and\n[`File::create`](`File::create`) methods are aliases for commonly used options using this\nbuilder.\n\nGenerally speaking, when using `OpenOptions`, you'll first call\n[`OpenOptions::new`](`OpenOptions::new`), then chain calls to methods to set each option, then\ncall [`OpenOptions::open`](`OpenOptions::open`), passing the path of the file you're trying to\nopen. This will give you a [`io::Result`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/type.Result.html) with a [`File`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/fs/struct.File.html) inside that you\ncan further operate on.\n\n# Examples\n\nOpening a file to read:\n\n```rust\nuse std::fs::OpenOptions;\n\nlet file = OpenOptions::new().read(true).open(\"foo.txt\");\n```\n\nOpening a file for both reading and writing, as well as creating it if it\ndoesn't exist:\n\n```rust\nuse std::fs::OpenOptions;\n\nlet file = OpenOptions::new()\n            .read(true)\n            .write(true)\n            .create(true)\n            .open(\"foo.txt\");\n```"}}}
