{"id":1936,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::fs::OpenOptions\n```\n\n```rust\npub fn create(&mut self, create: bool) -> &mut Self\n```\n\n---\n\nSets the option to create a new file, or open it if it already exists.\n\nIn order for the file to be created, [`OpenOptions::write`](`OpenOptions::write`) or\n[`OpenOptions::append`](`OpenOptions::append`) access must be used.\n\n# Examples\n\n```rust\nuse std::fs::OpenOptions;\n\nlet file = OpenOptions::new().write(true).create(true).open(\"foo.txt\");\n```"}}}
