{"id":1946,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::fs::OpenOptions\n```\n\n```rust\npub fn open<P>(&self, path: P) -> io::Result<File>\nwhere\n    P: AsRef<Path>,\n```\n\n---\n\nOpens a file at `path` with the options specified by `self`.\n\n# Errors\n\nThis function will return an error under a number of different\ncircumstances. Some of these error conditions are listed here, together\nwith their [`io::ErrorKind`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html). The mapping to [`io::ErrorKind`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html)s is not\npart of the compatibility contract of the function.\n\n* [`NotFound`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): The specified file does not exist and neither `create`\n  or `create_new` is set.\n* [`NotFound`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): One of the directory components of the file path does\n  not exist.\n* [`PermissionDenied`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): The user lacks permission to get the specified\n  access rights for the file.\n* [`PermissionDenied`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): The user lacks permission to open one of the\n  directory components of the specified path.\n* [`AlreadyExists`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): `create_new` was specified and the file already\n  exists.\n* [`InvalidInput`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html): Invalid combinations of open options (truncate\n  without write access, no access mode set, etc.).\n\nThe following errors don't match any existing [`io::ErrorKind`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html) at the moment:\n\n* One of the directory components of the specified file path\n  was not, in fact, a directory.\n* Filesystem-level errors: full disk, write permission\n  requested on a read-only file system, exceeded disk quota, too many\n  open files, too long filename, too many symbolic links in the\n  specified path (Unix-like systems only), etc.\n\n# Examples\n\n```rust\nuse std::fs::OpenOptions;\n\nlet file = OpenOptions::new().read(true).open(\"foo.txt\");\n```"}}}
