{"id":1995,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::io::Read\n```\n\n```rust\npub fn read_to_string(&mut self, buf: &mut String) -> Result<usize>\n```\n\n---\n\nRead all bytes until EOF in this source, appending them to `buf`.\n\nIf successful, this function returns the number of bytes which were read\nand appended to `buf`.\n\n# Errors\n\nIf the data in this stream is *not* valid UTF-8 then an error is\nreturned and `buf` is unchanged.\n\nSee [`read_to_end`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Read.html#method.read_to_end) for other error semantics.\n\n# Examples\n\n[`File`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/fs/struct.File.html)s implement `Read`:\n\n```rust\nuse std::io;\nuse std::io::prelude::*;\nuse std::fs::File;\n\nfn main() -> io::Result<()> {\n    let mut f = File::open(\"foo.txt\")?;\n    let mut buffer = String::new();\n\n    f.read_to_string(&mut buffer)?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n(See also the [`std::fs::read_to_string`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/fs/fn.read_to_string.html) convenience function for\nreading from a file.)"}}}
