{"id":2369,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::io::error\n```\n\n```rust\npub struct Error\n```\n\n---\n\nThe error type for I/O operations of the [`Read`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Read.html), [`Write`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Write.html), [`Seek`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Seek.html), and\nassociated traits.\n\nErrors mostly originate from the underlying OS, but custom instances of\n`Error` can be created with crafted error messages and a particular value of\n[`ErrorKind`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html)."}}}
