{"id":2409,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::fs::File\n```\n\n```rust\npub fn create<P>(path: P) -> io::Result<File>\nwhere\n    P: AsRef<Path>,\n```\n\n---\n\nOpens a file in write-only mode.\n\nThis function will create a file if it does not exist,\nand will truncate it if it does.\n\nSee the [`OpenOptions::open`](`OpenOptions::open`) function for more details.\n\n# Examples\n\n```rust\nuse std::fs::File;\n\nfn main() -> std::io::Result<()> {\n    let mut f = File::create(\"foo.txt\")?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```"}}}
