{"id":2419,"type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":{"kind":"markdown","value":"\n```rust\nstd::io::Write\n```\n\n```rust\npub fn write_all(&mut self, buf: &[u8]) -> Result<()>\n```\n\n---\n\nAttempts to write an entire buffer into this writer.\n\nThis method will continuously call [`write`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Write.html#tymethod.write) until there is no more data\nto be written or an error of non-[`ErrorKind::Interrupted`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html) kind is\nreturned. This method will not return until the entire buffer has been\nsuccessfully written or such an error occurs. The first error that is\nnot of [`ErrorKind::Interrupted`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html) kind generated from this method will be\nreturned.\n\nIf the buffer contains no data, this will never call [`write`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Write.html#tymethod.write).\n\n# Errors\n\nThis function will return the first error of\nnon-[`ErrorKind::Interrupted`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html) kind that [`write`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/trait.Write.html#tymethod.write) returns.\n\n# Examples\n\n```rust\nuse std::io::prelude::*;\nuse std::fs::File;\n\nfn main() -> std::io::Result<()> {\n    let mut buffer = File::create(\"foo.txt\")?;\n\n    buffer.write_all(b\"some bytes\")?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```"}}}
